    - [x] `dotnet build` 0 errors
    - [x] Verification approach documented for T136 wave-end gate
    - [x] `IMembershipResolverService` interface signature unchanged
    - [x] No new DI registrations / packages / Dataverse columns introduced (one IPostConfigureOptions&lt;MembershipOptions&gt; singleton only)
    - [x] Publish-size impact reported (negligible — one new class)
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    **Status**: ✅ COMPLETED 2026-06-30 (Wave 12 task 130)

    **Root cause**: `MembershipOptions.IncludedIdentityTables` defaulted to empty `List<>` (line 30). The `"Membership"` appsettings section is absent in every deployed environment (only in the gitignored `appsettings.Development.json.template`). Consequence: `MembershipFieldDiscoveryService.BuildDiscoveryResult` (line 280) returned every lookup as `IgnoredField` reason `target-table-not-in-identity-list` → `MembershipResolverService.ResolveAsync` short-circuited at `descriptors.Count == 0` (line 220) → empty response for every user.

    **Fix**: Added `MembershipOptionsDefaults : IPostConfigureOptions<MembershipOptions>` that seeds the 6 canonical identity tables (systemuser, contact, team, businessunit, account, sprk_organization) + 4 audit-field exclusions (createdby, modifiedby, createdonbehalfby, modifiedonbehalfby) ONLY when the bound list is empty. Registered in `MembershipModule.AddMembership`. Post-configure pattern (not property-initializer) because `IConfiguration.Bind` APPENDS to `List<T>` — operator-bound config must replace, not append; pinned by dedicated test.

    **Tests added** (per ADR-038):
    - `DiscoverAsync_WithPostConfiguredDefaultMembershipOptions_DiscoversMatterAssignmentFields` (regression-protection — would have caught the bug pre-fix)
    - `AddMembership_WithEmptyConfig_SeedsCanonicalDefaultsViaPostConfigure` (DI integration)
    - `AddMembership_WithOperatorBoundIdentityTables_DoesNotSeedDefaults` (operator-override-replaces-not-appends invariant)

    **Audit notes resolution** appended to `notes/audits/wave12-120-assistant-workspace.md` §8.

    **Commit**: `451603bac fix(bff/r7): seed canonical MembershipOptions defaults via post-configure (T130 root-cause fix)`

    **Unblocks T131**: DailyBriefingCollector can now refactor away from inline FetchXml `eq-userid` bypass.

    **Post-deploy verification reserved for T136 wave-end gate**: smoke `GET /api/users/me/memberships/sprk_matter` for 3 test users with known matter assignments; expect non-zero responses.
  </notes>
</task>
